                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>“We continue to look for solutions in our clinical trials. Our goal has been and continues to be identifying ways to meet people where they are in their ability to preserve their vision, and our clinical trials are looking at ways to provide glaucoma patients additional options,” says Robinson.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Robinson and his team’s work isn’t over. They continue to collaborate with key opinion leaders in the field of glaucoma care while also connecting with people living with glaucoma and their caregivers so they have access to resources so they can better understand their eye health.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“We will always incorporate patient needs into our science&amp;nbsp;and partnering with well-known voices in eye care to frontline ophthalmologists will allow us to help more people continue to see clearly.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
